<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-59-0951 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author reviews what Hawaii is doing to reach its two goals: to comeas close as possible to becoming electrical energy self-sufficient andto become at least 90% energy self-sufficient by the year 2005. Renewableenergy is one area Hawaii is successfully pursuing. Conservation is anotherarea. Windmills, biomass, a geothermal well, and solar water heatersare all in use in Hawaii. The author says everyone must do his part toexplore new forms of energy and to conserve the energy Hawaii has.</TEXT></DOC>